excerpt: Iconic, energy-efficient tower block with a distinctive twisted shell, home to offices & apartments.
detail_description: Turning Torso is a remarkable and energy-efficient tower block located in Vastra hamnen, Malmo. Designed by Santiago Calatrava, this neo-futurist skyscraper stands at 190 meters with 54 stories, making it the tallest building in the Nordics. Its distinctive twisted shell turns 90 degrees from bottom to top, creating a magnificent sight for visitors.
name: Turning Torso

detail_description: The Disgusting Food Museum in Malmo is not just a quirky attraction, but also an exploration of the concept of disgusting food and how attitudes towards it can change. With 80 foods from around the world on display, visitors have the opportunity to taste some of these perceived delicacies for themselves. Created by Andreas Ahrens and Samuel West, who also founded the Museum of Failure, this museum aims to delve into the emotion of disgust and its role in human culture.
name: Disgusting Food Museum

excerpt: Built 1869–1870, the 8.4-hectare English-style park features a cast iron fountain & cycling trails.
detail_description: Kungsparken in Malmö is an 8.4-hectare English-style park built between 1869 and 1870, featuring a cast iron fountain and cycling trails. It's a lush green space adjacent to the castle grounds, boasting stunning gardens, numerous statues, two lakes, and a charming community garden. The park offers a peaceful retreat with meandering paths for leisurely strolls and opportunities for picnics.
name: Kungsparken, Malmö

excerpt: This fortress was built by King Christian III of Denmark & replaced one from the previous century.
detail_description: Malmö Castle, built by King Christian III of Denmark to replace an earlier fortress, is a unique sight in the cosmopolitan city. It features red walls and a remaining moat, dating back to the 16th century and being the oldest-preserved Renaissance castle in the Nordic countries. Today, it houses various themed museums with permanent and temporary exhibitions including paintings, period furniture, historic clothing, an aquarium in the basement, and even a volcano simulation.
name: Malmö Castle

detail_description: Lilla Torg, which means "small square," may not stand out on a map, but it is a popular destination for tourists. The cobblestone square is surrounded by charming restaurants and cafes that offer outdoor seating in the summer. This creates a lively atmosphere that showcases the best of Malmo. Additionally, during the summer months, numerous food stalls converge on the square, making it one of Malmö's top attractions.
name: Lilla torg

excerpt: Brick Gothic church with flying buttresses mostly dating to the 14th & 15th centuries.
detail_description: When it comes to Protestant churches, one cannot go wrong by visiting St. Peter's Church in Goran Olstagan. This historical church is steeped in history and features beautiful bright Romanesque inspired interiors that are sure to please visitors of all faiths. Besides its historical significance, the church also boasts charming displays, chandeliers, and sacred sculptures that make it a must-see for anyone visiting the area.
name: St. Peter's Church

excerpt: Modern & contemporary art museum, designed by Rafael Moneo, with Picassos & photography collection.
detail_description: In the vibrant city of Malmo, Sweden, art enthusiasts should make a point to visit Moderna Museet Malmö. This contemporary art museum, designed by Rafael Moneo, showcases an impressive collection of modern and contemporary artworks including pieces by renowned artists such as Picasso and Andy Warhol. The museum's striking orange-washed building hosts diverse exhibitions and installations from the 20th century to the present day.
name: Moderna Museet Malmö

excerpt: Gallery for changing exhibitions of modern art by major names, plus a bookstore & restaurant.
detail_description: Malmö Konsthall is a leading exhibition hall for contemporary art in Europe, featuring changing exhibitions by major artists. Since its establishment in 1975, the venue has embodied architect Klas Anshelm's vision of a spacious concrete box that integrates with the surrounding park and natural light. With 2,000 square meters of exhibition space, Malmö Konsthall hosts three to four exhibitions annually. The gallery also houses a bookstore and restaurant for visitors to enjoy.
name: Malmö Konsthall

detail_description: Folkets Park is a vibrant and diverse destination offering something for everyone. The park features Moriska Paviljongen, where visitors can enjoy after-work drinks and a buffet, with vegetarian and vegan options available. Additionally, the park boasts a variety of amenities such as playgrounds for children, a bierhaus-style venue like Mikeller, beautiful gardens, picnic spots, theaters, and green spaces. It's an inclusive space catering to different interests and age groups.
name: Folkets Park

excerpt: Castlelike 1901 library building set in riverside parkland, with a modern glass extension & a cafe.
detail_description: The Malmö City Library is a captivating structure located in a riverside park, featuring a blend of historic and modern architecture. Comprising three distinct buildings, including The Castle with its Renaissance-inspired design, The Cylinder housing the entrance and a cozy cafe, and The Calendar of Light which hosts the main book collection and study areas. The library offers an engaging space for both children and adults, with a dedicated kids' area in The Castle and impressive glass architecture in The Calendar of Light.
name: Malmö City Library

excerpt: Malmö is a coastal city in southern Sweden. It lies at the eastern end of the striking Öresund Bridge, a long road and railway bridge–tunnel running to Copenhagen, Denmark. In the city center, Lilla Torg is a cobblestone square with cafes, half-timbered houses and shops selling local handicrafts. Malmö Castle, a 16th-century fortress built by King Christian III of Denmark, houses nature, history and art exhibits.
detail_description: Malmö, a coastal city in southern Sweden, is known for its striking Öresund Bridge connecting it to Copenhagen, Denmark. The city center features the charming cobblestone square of Lilla Torg with cafes and shops selling local handicrafts. Malmö Castle, a 16th-century fortress, houses nature, history and art exhibits. The area near Mollevanstorget offers a diverse cultural experience with a young population and foreign ancestry.
name: Malmö

excerpt: Large green space with ponds, jogging paths, picnic areas & occasional seasonal concerts.
detail_description: Pildammsparken is a beloved 45-hectare park in Malmo, offering a serene escape from the city's hustle and bustle. It features ponds, jogging paths, and picnic areas, making it a popular spot for both locals and tourists. The park hosts outdoor movie nights, concerts, and music festivals during the summer months.
name: Pildammsparken

excerpt: Vibrant park area featuring grassy fields, expansive gardens, a windmill & a cafe.
detail_description: Slottsträdgården is a charming park area in Malmo, often compared to a smaller version of Central Park. Divided by the Malmo canal, it connects the surrounding neighborhoods with picturesque walking and biking paths. The park features expansive gardens, grassy fields, a windmill, and a cafe called Slottstradgardens Kafe. Families can enjoy playgrounds and various exploration spots while strolling through the many inviting grass fields and benches.
name: Slottsträdgården

excerpt: Food counters serving ramen, ice cream, falafel & poke in a repurposed dockside industrial space.
detail_description: Malmö Saluhall is a vibrant food hall located in a repurposed dockside industrial space, offering an array of culinary delights. Visitors can indulge in a variety of cuisines including ramen, ice cream, falafel, and poke from the diverse food counters. The bustling atmosphere is complemented by cool restaurants, cafes, a bakery, tea shop, and even a flower stand.
name: Malmö Saluhall

detail_description: Möllevångstorget is a vibrant square where you can immerse yourself in a diverse cultural experience. The area is bustling with vendors offering an array of affordable fresh fruits and vegetables. As you explore the surroundings, you'll come across an assortment of Asian and Middle Eastern shops, each showcasing unique specialty products that are sure to pique your interest.
name: Möllevångstorget

excerpt: Bustling Gamla Staden is Malmö’s historic heart, known for Malmö Castle, a red-brick fortress surrounded by parkland and a moat, and squares like Stortorget and Gustav Adolfs Torg, lined with centuries-old buildings. The Moderna Museet is in a former power plant, and St. Peter’s Church has a chapel with medieval wall paintings. The area is scattered with half-timbered houses, souvenir shops, and boutiques.
detail_description: Gamla Staden, the historic heart of Malmö, is a bustling area filled with centuries-old buildings and attractions. The red-brick fortress of Malmö Castle stands surrounded by parkland and a moat, while squares like Stortorget and Gustav Adolfs Torg are lined with charming old buildings. Visitors can explore the former power plant housing the Moderna Museet and admire the medieval wall paintings in St. Peter’s Church.
name: Gamla staden

detail_description: Stortorget is a picturesque square in Malmo, surrounded by elegant buildings dating back to the 16th century. This charming oasis features cobblestone streets, colorful facades, and lively cafes where locals embrace the art of fika (coffee break). The square is home to an equestrian statue and hosts large-scale events.
name: Storgatan

excerpt:
Ribersborg is a neighbourhood of Malmö, Sweden, situated in the Borough of Västra Innerstaden, Malmö Municipality, Skåne County.
At its seaside, there is the Ribersborgs kallbadhus, a protected historic wooden pier used for open-air bathing and sauna use. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Ribersborg, located in the Västra Innerstaden borough of Malmö, Sweden, is a charming neighborhood known for its iconic Ribersborg Kallbadhus. This historic bathhouse, over a century old, is a prominent landmark in the city. The area also offers a long stretch with small snack bars and restrooms along with bars for bathing, providing visitors with stunning views of the Oresund Bridge.
name: Ribersborg

detail_description: Malmö - Lilla Torg is a charming and picturesque square in the heart of Malmö, comparable in size to Utrecht in the Netherlands. The square is adorned with old buildings, a telephone booth, and a water pump, exuding an atmospheric provincial city vibe. It is located next to Malmö's main square and is surrounded by colorful buildings, restaurants, and cafes.
name: Malmö - Lilla Torg

detail_description: The impressive town hall in the heart of Malmo's Old Town was built in the 1500s and has a more modern stucco look. It was renovated during 1860, with the Dutch Renaissance exterior coming from this time period.
name: Malmö City Hall

detail_description: Ribersborgsstranden, also known as The Ribersborg Beach, is a picturesque white sandy beach in Malmo, Sweden. It stretches along the coastline and offers stunning views of the Oresund Bridge and the iconic Turning Torso skyscraper. The area around Ribersborgsstranden is perfect for exploration with its quiet roads, marinas, piers, and swanky condos/apartment buildings. There are also bike paths leading to a small beach area by the water.
name: Ribersborgsstranden

detail_description: Gamla Väster, the historic district of Malmo, is a must-visit destination for travelers. One of its highlights is Noir Coffee Culture, where visitors can indulge in a delightful breakfast spread featuring an array of options such as avocado toast, croissants, pastries, and of course, exceptional coffee.
name: Gamla Väster

detail_description: Malmo Live Concert AB is a renowned live music venue located in the heart of Malmo, Sweden. The concert hall is celebrated for its exceptional acoustics and hosts a variety of performances including classical concerts, contemporary music events, and cultural festivals. Adjacent to Malmo Live, this multifunctional cultural complex offers a unique experience for music enthusiasts and cultural connoisseurs.
name: Malmo Live Concert AB

excerpt: Västra hamnen is a neighbourhood of Malmö, situated in the borough of Centrum, Malmö Municipality, Skåne County, Sweden. This sub-area is an artificial island. It is a residential, educational and industrial area in Malmö. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Västra hamnen, located in Malmö, Sweden, was once an industrial area but has undergone a transformation into one of the city's most exclusive neighborhoods. The former industrial zone is now a family-friendly area with charming cafes, playgrounds, and a beach. Visitors can enjoy leisurely strolls along the wooden walkways by the sea or explore the new skate park.
name: Västra hamnen

excerpt: Cobblestone pedestrian street with various stores & upscale boutiques, plus bars & restaurants.
detail_description: Södergatan is a charming cobblestone pedestrian street in Malmo, lined with a variety of stores, upscale boutiques, bars, and restaurants. It is the main shopping street in Malmö's Gamla Staden and offers a diverse range of unique souvenirs, cozy home items, and the latest fashions. The area is known for its trendy shops catering to all ages and tastes.
name: Södergatan

excerpt: Meeting place for rotating exhibits related to design, crafts & architecture, plus a shop & a cafe.
detail_description: Form/Design Center is a hub for ever-changing displays showcasing design, crafts, and architecture. Situated in Lilla Torg, the heart of the Old Town's design district, it features a cafe and shop offering an array of easily transportable gifts such as carved wooden spoons, soft suede and leather bags, and ceramics. The center hosts temporary exhibitions on two floors with a focus on sustainability and environmentally-friendly practices.
name: Form/Design Center

excerpt: Built 1903–1907, this art nouveau Lutheran church features wood- & stone-carved roses inside & out.
detail_description: St. John's Church, also known as Sankt Johannes Kyrka, is a stunning Lutheran church in Malmo, Sweden. Built between 1903 and 1907, it showcases exquisite art nouveau design with intricate wood and stone-carved roses both inside and outside the building. Unlike traditional churches, the architect placed the tower and armory on the north side to symbolize a new era. The church's red brick exterior contrasts with its serene and simple interior featuring softer colors.
name: St. John's Church

excerpt: Möllevången, also called Möllan, is a neighbourhood of Malmö, situated in the Borough of Södra Innerstaden, Malmö Municipality, Skåne County, Sweden. It covers an area of 53 hectares, bordered by five streets: Bergsgatan, Amiralsgatan, Nobelvägen and Spårvägsgatan/Södra Förstadsgatan. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Möllevången, also known as Möllan, is a vibrant neighborhood in Malmö, Sweden. It has a diverse population and a lively atmosphere with great food, bars, and shops. The area is renowned for its Middle Eastern food scene and hosts a bustling market offering fresh produce, spice mixtures, dried fruit, and nuts. The neighborhood's main square exudes an energetic vibe reminiscent of a Middle Eastern bazaar. Additionally, the surrounding streets are lined with top-notch restaurants.
name: Möllevången

detail_description: Malmö Centralstation is a fascinating blend of old and new architecture, featuring preserved brick walls alongside a modern glass and steel terminal. With over 150 years of history, the station has been continuously upgraded while maintaining its heritage. The serene canal nearby offers a peaceful retreat from the bustling station. It's easy to navigate with platforms for Oresundstag and Regional trains, lifts for luggage, and self-service ticket machines.
name: Malmö Centralstation

excerpt:
Davidshall is a neighbourhood of Malmö, situated in the Borough of Centrum, Malmö Municipality, Skåne County, Sweden.
The urban plan for the area was drawn up in 1924 by the then city engineer Erik Bülow-Hübe. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Davidshall is a charming neighborhood located in the Borough of Centrum, Malmö Municipality, Skåne County, Sweden. The urban plan for this area was designed back in 1924 by the city engineer Erik Bülow-Hübe. If you're strolling just a couple of blocks from gagatan, you'll find yourself in Davidshall district where you can discover an array of vintage and independent shops. A shared Instagram account highlights these unique shops and provides ample inspiration for visitors.
name: Davidshall

excerpt: Large complex with a wide range of museums & buildings exploring history, culture & seafaring.
detail_description: Malmo Museum, situated in Malmo, Sweden, is a cultural gem that offers an immersive exploration of the region's history, art, and natural heritage. Located near Malmohus Castle in central Malmo, the museum boasts a diverse range of exhibits and interactive displays that delve into the city's artistic achievements, historical roots, and natural environment.
name: Malmo Museum

excerpt: Longtime park with a playground, eateries & open-air events, such as markets & concerts.
detail_description: Folkets Park in Malmo is a historic park that offers a range of activities for visitors. It features a playground, Adventure Golf, Cool Minds science center, Reptile Centre, and a skate park, making it an ideal destination for families. Additionally, the park houses a dance studio, cultural center, cafes, outdoor eateries and even an ice-skating rink during winter.
name: Folkets Park Malmö

detail_description: Gustav Adolfs Torg is located in the heart of Malmo, near Stortorget. This pedestrian street leads to Sodertull and eventually to Triangeln, a popular shopping mall. From there, visitors can easily access transportation options such as trains and buses to reach destinations like Hyllie, home to the expansive Emporia shopping mall.
name: Gustav Adolfs torg

detail_description: Drottningtorget is a haven for eco-conscious shoppers. At Morot & Annat, you can browse through a diverse selection of organically produced textiles and fresh produce. Just around the corner, Uma Bazaar offers a variety of fair-trade clothing crafted by a women's collective in India. Whether you're looking for sustainable fashion or organic goods, this vibrant marketplace has something to offer for everyone with an environmentally friendly mindset.
name: Drottningtorget

excerpt: Massive indoor mall with unique free-form glass architecture, many shops & a food court.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant Hyllie neighborhood, Emporia Shopping Center stands as a beacon of modern retail and architectural brilliance. Spanning an impressive 70,000 square meters, this massive indoor mall boasts over 160 shops, restaurants, and cafes that cater to every shopping whim imaginable—from fashion to home decor. Designed by renowned architect Gert Wingardh, its striking wave-like exterior and amber-hued entrance create a visual spectacle that beckons visitors inside.
name: Emporia Shopping Center

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Malmö, Slottsparken is a sprawling green haven that invites visitors to unwind amidst its serene beauty. This expansive park features winding paths lined with lush trees and vibrant flowerbeds, creating an idyllic setting for leisurely strolls or playful afternoons with children. At its center stands the striking Pegasus statue by Carl Milles, while a charming Japanese garden adds an exotic touch to the landscape.
name: Slottsparken

detail_description: Apoteket Lejonet, also known as Lion Pharmacy, has been in operation since 1897 and is a fascinating piece of living history. Visitors are welcome to step inside, admire the stunning decor, and take photos without disturbing the customers. The pharmacy's beautiful interior has been likened to something out of a Harry Potter movie, making it a must-see for tourists. Conveniently located near the city hall, it also offers tax-free shopping for tourists.
name: Apoteket Lejonet

detail_description: Castle Mill, also known as Slottsmollan in Swedish, is a historical smock mill located in the Castle Park (Slottsparken) in Malmo. Built in 1851 on the remains of the Stenbock bastion, this well-preserved gem offers a fascinating glimpse into the region's history. While regular operation ceased in 1945, it now falls under the administration of the Malmo museum.
name: Castle Mill

detail_description: Söderberg & Sara is a popular bakery located in the Vastra Sorgenfri area of Malmo, next to St. Pauli kyrkogard. The café follows the New Nordic ethos by using organic flour, local produce, and even growing some fresh ingredients at its own farm. The menu features sourdough breads, cardamom buns, and wood-fired pizza. It's known for being a crowded spot with a village-like feel and is dog-friendly.
name: Söderberg & Sara

detail_description: Fiskehoddorna, also known as Malmo's fish market, is a row of colorful stalls offering fresh fish and seafood caught along the Oresund strait or up the West Coast. Each stall has its own specialty, whether it's specific types of fish or unique preparations like pickling or smoking. The market provides a cozy fishing village atmosphere and the opportunity to chat with local fishermen for insights into the waters of Oresund and Kattegat.
name: Fiskehoddorna

detail_description: The establishment is tidy, spacious, and comfortable. A review of their signature grilled burger, the "Jonas special," reveals that while it was generally satisfactory, the meat had an undercooked center and a slightly burned exterior. However, the restaurant offers plenty of other options ranging from 40kr to 100kr. The vegetarian choices are particularly appealing with a selection of burgers including halloumi and falafel served alongside fresh vegetables and parsley for added flavor and vitamin C.
name: GoGo Grill & Green

detail_description: Graffiti Hangaren is a contemporary art gallery in Malmo city that showcases street art from around the world. The gallery is located in an old warehouse and has been transforming the whole city into an urban art exhibition with murals and sculptures all over town.
name: Graffiti Hangaren

detail_description: Flixbus Stop is a convenient and well-equipped transportation hub that offers a range of amenities for travelers. It provides a comfortable waiting area with seating, restrooms, and sometimes even cafes or shops. The stop is strategically located in various cities, making it easily accessible for passengers to board their Flixbus coaches. With its clean and modern facilities, Flixbus Stop ensures that passengers have a pleasant experience while waiting for their bus to arrive.
name: Flixbus Stop
address: Central Station, Norra Vallgatan, 211 22 Malmö, Sweden

detail_description: Stortorget stands as one of Malmö's most celebrated and photographed squares, capturing the essence of the city’s rich history. At its center, you'll find a striking statue of King Karl X Gustav, a symbol of Swedish conquest. The square is framed by impressive architecture, including the grand Malmö Radhus. Throughout the year, Stortorget buzzes with life as it hosts various events and festivals that draw both locals and visitors alike to experience its vibrant atmosphere.
name: Stortorget

excerpt: Huge bridge linking the coast of Sweden with an artificial island with a tunnel to Denmark.
detail_description: The Øresund Bridge, opened in 2000, is a remarkable engineering feat that connects the coast of Sweden to an artificial island with a tunnel leading to Denmark. It is the longest bridge in Europe and consists of both a motorway and railway line. The bridge spans 8km across the Øresund strait to an artificial island before transitioning into the Drogden Tunnel, which extends underwater for an additional 4km.
name: Øresund Bridge

detail_description: The Knotted Gun, also known as the Non-Violence sculpture, is a poignant piece of art created by Swedish artist Carl Fredrik Reutersward. Erected in memory of John Lennon shortly after his tragic death, this bronze statue features a handgun with its barrel intricately tied in a knot. This striking imagery serves as a powerful reminder of the importance of peace and social justice.
name: The Knotted Gun / Non Violence

excerpt: Large venue for sporting events & concerts, plus  conferences & events, with dining options.
detail_description: Malmö Arena is a versatile venue that hosts various events such as sporting competitions, concerts, conferences, and family shows. It features a restaurant area with 3,250 seats and 20 fast food outlets. The arena is also the home field of the local hockey team Redhawks. Visitors can enjoy world-class performances by renowned artists in solo concerts. Situated in the Oresund Region, it offers top-notch facilities for wining and dining or grabbing a quick snack.
name: Malmö Arena

excerpt: Square with a statue commemorating the labor movement & market stalls selling fruit & vegetables.
detail_description: Möllevångstorget, located in the heart of Malmo, is a vibrant square known for its bustling market stalls offering an array of fresh fruits, vegetables, and flowers. The surrounding area boasts a diverse culinary scene with restaurants serving cuisine from around the world including India, Iran, Afghanistan, and Thailand. Additionally, visitors can explore an eclectic mix of shops selling everything from jewelry to specialty foods. The square also serves as a gathering place for demonstrations and events.
name: Möllevångstorget

excerpt: Dotted with benches, the tree-lined avenues of this canalside cemetery are popular for strolls.
name: Malmö old cemetery
